					<head>Commentaries</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>The commentary of Japheth ben Ali ha-Levi on the Song of Songs and Ruth (fragments).</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="ara">Hebrew, Arabic</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="95v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perushim </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרושים</title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="en">Japheth ben Ali, ha-Levi,‏ active 10th century  </persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="he">יפת בן עלי, הלוי</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>The volume contains the Hebrew text of the Book of Ruth and the Song of Songs in an Arabic phonetic transcription, with an Arabic translation and Yefet&apos;s commentary.</p>
								<p>The scribal subscription, folio 95v, shows that the manuscript was written in Yefet's lifetime, i.e. in the early 11th century.</p>
							</note>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="1v" to="25v"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Ruth</title>
								<note>
									<p>Missing chapters 3:3-4:10.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="25v" to="95v"/>
								<note>
									<p>Missing chapters 3:9-5:14.</p>
								</note>
								<title xml:lang="en">Song of Songs</title>
							</msItem>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the beginning of the 11th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex. </support>
								<extent>95 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>230</height>
										<width>180</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>160</height>
										<width>140</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>95 folios (+ 1 paper flyleaf at the beginning and 2 at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires originally of 10 leaves each, divided into 2 parts of 4 and 11 quires respectively. </p>
									<p>Most of the quires are now imperfect. </p>
									<p>The quires are signed with Arabic letters on the left-hand upper corner of the first page. A separate enumeration is used for each of the two parts. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>Lacunae after folios: 12, 21, 31, 45, 48, 61, 115.<p>Partially water-damaged.</p>
									<p>Sings of worm-eating.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="11 15" writtenLines="11 15">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>The diacritic points are generally added. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>A Naskhi hand of the early 11th century. </summary>
